========================================================
        JENKINS EMAIL NOTIFICATION COMPLETE GUIDE
========================================================

This file contains detailed steps to configure
Jenkins to send email notifications using Gmail.

You can follow this anytime in the future.

--------------------------------------------------------
1. REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------
- Gmail account
- 2-Step Verification enabled in Gmail
- Jenkins Email Extension Plugin installed
- 16-digit Gmail App Password (NOT normal password)
- Jenkins server running

--------------------------------------------------------
2. CREATE GMAIL APP PASSWORD
--------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1: Go to https://myaccount.google.com
STEP 2: Click "Security"
STEP 3: Enable "2-Step Verification"
STEP 4: After enabling, go to:
        Security → App Passwords
STEP 5: Select "Other (Custom name)"
STEP 6: Enter:
        Jenkins-Email
STEP 7: Click "Generate"
STEP 8: Copy the 16-digit password (example):
        abcd efgh ijkl mnop
SAVE IT — this will be used inside Jenkins.

--------------------------------------------------------
3. INSTALL EMAIL EXTENSION PLUGIN IN JENKINS
--------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1: Jenkins → Manage Jenkins
STEP 2: Manage Plugins
STEP 3: "Available" tab
STEP 4: Search:
        Email Extension Plugin
STEP 5: Install it
STEP 6: Restart Jenkins if required

--------------------------------------------------------
4. CONFIGURE GLOBAL EMAIL SETTINGS (VERY IMPORTANT)
--------------------------------------------------------

Go to:
    Jenkins Dashboard → Manage Jenkins → Configure System

Scroll down until you see:
    "E-mail Notification"

Fill EXACTLY like this:

    SMTP Server:
        smtp.gmail.com

    Use SMTP Authentication:
        ✔ CHECK THIS BOX

    User Name:
        your Gmail ID (example: abc@gmail.com)

    Password:
        paste your 16-digit Gmail App Password

    Use SSL:
        ✔ CHECK THIS BOX

    SMTP Port:
        465

    Reply-To Address:
        your Gmail ID

-----------------------------------------------
TEST GLOBAL EMAIL SETTINGS
-----------------------------------------------
You will see a button:

    "Test configuration by sending test email"

Click it → enter any email → click send.

If correct, you receive a test email.

--------------------------------------------------------
5. CONFIGURE EXTENDED EMAIL NOTIFICATION
--------------------------------------------------------

Still inside:
    Manage Jenkins → Configure System

Scroll further down until you find:
    "Extended E-mail Notification"

Now fill:

    SMTP Server:
        smtp.gmail.com

    SMTP Port:
        465

    Use SSL:
        ✔ CHECK THIS

    Credentials:
        Add your Gmail ID + App Password
        (Click 'Add' → kind: Username/Password)

    Default Content Type:
        text/html

Click "Save".

--------------------------------------------------------
6. HOW TO CREATE A JENKINS JOB (REQUIRED BEFORE EMAIL)
--------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: Open Jenkins Dashboard
STEP 2: Click:
        New Item
STEP 3: Enter the job name:
        example: email_test_job
STEP 4: Select:
        Freestyle project
STEP 5: Click:
        OK

You are now on the job configuration page.

--------------------------------------------------------
6A. ENABLE EMAIL IN YOUR JENKINS JOB
--------------------------------------------------------

This controls WHEN email should be sent.
You must do this for each job.

STEP 1: Open Jenkins Dashboard
STEP 2: Click your job name (example: email_test_job)
STEP 3: Click:
        Configure
STEP 4: Scroll down to:
        Post-build Actions
STEP 5: Click:
        Add post-build action
STEP 6: Select:
        Editable Email Notification

Fill:

A. Project Recipient List:
        your-email@gmail.com

B. Content Type:
        text/html

C. Default Subject/Body:
        (optional – leave empty)

--------------------------------------------------------
6B. ENABLE EMAIL TRIGGERS (VERY IMPORTANT)
--------------------------------------------------------

Inside "Editable Email Notification":

STEP 1: Click:
        Add Trigger

Choose from these options:
    - Always
    - Success
    - Failure
    - Unstable
    - Still Failing
    - Before Build

Recommended:
    ✔ Success
    ✔ Failure

STEP 2: Select:
        Failure → Add
        Success → Add

STEP 3: Scroll down
STEP 4: Click:
        Save

--------------------------------------------------------
7. TEST EMAIL NOTIFICATIONS
--------------------------------------------------------

TEST 1: SUCCESS EMAIL
    - Click:
          Build Now
    - Build succeeds
    - You get a "Build Success" email

TEST 2: FAILURE EMAIL
    - Add invalid command in build step:
          abcdefxyz
    - Build fails
    - You get a "Build Failure" email

--------------------------------------------------------
8. CONFIRM EVERYTHING IS WORKING
--------------------------------------------------------

You must see:

1. Test email works in "Configure System"
2. Jenkins sends email on SUCCESS
3. Jenkins sends email on FAILURE
4. Emails arrive instantly in Gmail
5. Job configuration shows:
       Editable Email Notification

--------------------------------------------------------
9. NOTES
--------------------------------------------------------

- Webhooks are NOT required for email setup.
  Email will work even without GitHub.

- Webhooks + email together:
      GitHub Push → Jenkins Build → Email Sent

- Most common issue is wrong App Password.
  Must be 16 characters, no spaces.

========================================================
        END OF JENKINS EMAIL NOTIFICATION GUIDE
========================================================
